    <!-- BG1 -->
    <section>
    <div class="row splitRow filler " data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration='1500'>
        <div class="column bg1">
            <h2>What is <u>interconnectedness</u> ?</h2>
            <p class = 'p-less'>The Cambridge Dictionary (n.d.) defines interconnectedness as <u class = 'highlighter1'>“the state of having different parts or things connected 
                or related to each other”.</u> It is the condition where events from completely far and different circumstances have spillover 
                effects to people in different places. These spillover effects may be negative or positive. Either way, it is <u class = 'highlighter1'>significant in 
                affecting the lives of other people (Heywood, 2011). </u></p>
        </div>
        <div class="column content-1">
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>
    <!-- BG2 -->
    <section>
    <div class="row splitRow filler  " data-aos="fade-left" data-aos-duration='1500'>
        <div class="column content-2">
        </div>
        <div class="column col-color bg2">
            <h2>What is <u>interdependence</u> ?</h2>
            <p class='p-less'>
                It is defined as <u class='highlighter2'>“the fact of depending on each other” (Cambridge Dictionary, n.d.).</u> According to Heywood (2011), two parties are bound in a relationship where a decision 
                made by either of the parties would have an <u class='highlighter2'>influence on the other party.</u> 
                <br><br>
                This is said to have stemmed from the sense of mutual vulnerability. 
                It is commonly observed in world politics where countries would enter into economic <u class='highlighter2'>cooperation and integration to address issues together.</u>
                </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>
    <!-- BG3 -->
    <section>
    <div class="row splitRow filler" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration='1500'>
        <div class="column col-color bg3">
            <h2><u>Interconnectedness</u> in our world today...</h2>
            <p class='p-more'>
                The world today seems to have shrunk as events in distant places have shown <u class='highlighter3'>repercussions to the life of people across the globe (Heywood, 2011 : Bova, 2012). </u>
                In recent years, advanced technology in transport and communication have closed <u class='highlighter3'>the gap on distance between borders (Bova, 2012).</u> 
                <br><br>
                Within the context of today’s global landscape, our interconnectedness has  <u class='highlighter3'>migrated to a new medium— the internet.</u> 
                With the risks involved in going outside due to the ongoing pandemic, the safest means to connect to <u class='highlighter3'>the world is online.</u> 
                Work, studies, investments, and more have shifted to an online platform, highlighting <u class='highlighter3'>the link that binds us to the world.</u>
                </p>
        </div>
        <div class="column content-3">
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>
    <!-- BG4 -->
    <section>
    <div class="row splitRow filler" data-aos="fade-left" data-aos-duration='1500'>
        <div class="column content-4">
        </div>
        <div class="column bg1">
            <h2>Finding <u>interdependence</u> today...</h2>
            <p class='p-more'>
                Economic cooperation and integration among nations has changed the landscape of trade and commerce. Today, we can observe the interdependence of ASEAN countries in trade where inter-regional tariffs 
                were remarkably cut under the  ASEAN Free Trade Area (AFTA) (ASEAN, n.d.).  
                <br><br>
                Right now, we can observe interdependence with the <u class = 'highlighter1'>global effort in vaccine production and circulation.</u> Research and development on attaining methods to reduce the spread of COVID is <u class='highlighter1'>shared with the global community</u>, 
                establishing the fact that the world is <u class='highlighter1'>united against a common threat.</u> This signifies that dependence exceeds the needs of man but <u class='highlighter1'>as a collective whole.</u>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    </section>
    <!-- BG5 -->
    <section>

    <div class="row splitRow filler " data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration='1500'>
        <div class="column col-color bg2">
            <h2>What can we <u>look forward</u> to?</h2>
            <p class='p-normal'>As history is unfolding in front of us, each and every one of us is looking forward to easing our way into the lives we lived before this pandemic. With this in mind, we find ourselves in a position to <u class='highlighter2'>contribute to the global effort</u> being exerted by each nation in this world. 
                <br><br>
                Within the context of interconnectedness and interdependence, it’s up to us, the residents of our country and this world, to wear masks, get vaccinated, and so much more. As mentioned,  <u class='highlighter2'>we can positively or negatively affect</u> the lives of others where our lives, as well as the 
                lives of the people around us, is <u class='highlighter2'>dependent on the decisions</u> that we and they make.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="column content-5">
        </div>
    </div>        
    </section>
    <!-- SECTION 2 -->
    <div class='container justify-content-center greet-cont' data-aos="zoom-in"  data-aos-duration='1000'>
